&lt;p&gt;Takealot Fulfilment Solutions (TFS), a division of Takealot Online (RF) (Pty) Ltd, is looking for a highly talented&lt;strong&gt; Automation Project Manage&lt;/strong&gt;r&amp;nbsp;to join our team in &lt;strong&gt;Cape Town&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join Our Mission at Takealot Fulfilment Solutions | We Are TFS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Revolutionising e-commerce logistics in South Africa with cutting-edge technology and operational excellence. We deliver 30+ million orders annually, empowering businesses and driving economic growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We&#39;re Looking For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Innovative, ambitious individuals ready to shape the future of e-commerce logistics. At TFS, &quot;Uniquely You&quot; meets &quot;Powerfully Us&quot;, where your individuality strengthens our collective mission.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At TFS, your growth is our growth. You&#39;ll be joining a team powered by Takealot Group&#39;s core values.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position reports to the Head : Infrastructure and Automation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Purpose of the role: Responsible for the project management of automation and mechanisation projects within the Distribution Centres (DC’s) in the Takealot and TFS network, with &lt;strong&gt;reporting responsibility to the Head: Infrastructure and Automation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The function of the role is to evaluate technology, execute the planning, designing and implementation of new systems and automated infrastructure improvements in the DC’s from start to completion, inclusive of hand over to the operational team and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;distant support thereof. The responsibility will also include TFS fulfilment facilities as well as TFS clients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is required to, on an ongoing basis, evaluate existing processes and infrastructure to ensure that maximum efficiency is extracted through improvement projects. The role manages project expenditures against budget allocation for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;specific projects, under the guidance of the Head: Strategy and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities: (What are you directly responsible to achieve within the scope of your role)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Designing and implementing mechanisation infrastructure to either support the business growth or bring optimization to an existing process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Procurement of equipment to support operations and processes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to draft request for proposal (RFP) documents&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyzing and implementing new automation within the distribution center operations, under the guidance of the Head: Strategy and Infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Management and control of costs for specific projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build viability study for new projects, that proves ROI based on elements that will be improved or affected by the project implementation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supplier engagement and management in accordance with contractually agreed terms&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stakeholder engagement with Operational staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Required Qualification:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelors Degree / B-Tech Engineering qualification – Mechatronic, Electrical or Mechanical&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in a project space in Distribution Centres, production environment or warehousing on a large scale with complex operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3-5 years Automation experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills, knowledge &amp;amp; abilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent problem-solving skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of Distribution Centre purpose, function and operation at a detail level&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;l

&lt;p&gt;The Takealot Group, a leading South African online retailer, is looking for a highly talented &lt;strong&gt;BI Engineer &lt;/strong&gt;to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a young, dynamic, hyper growth company looking for smart, creative, hard-working people with integrity to join us!&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At the Takealot Group (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.takealot.com/&quot;&gt;Takealot.com&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;amp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.mrdfood.com/&quot;&gt; Mr D&lt;/a&gt;), the BI Engineer works closely with our internal stakeholders to determine their business intelligence, reporting and data analysis needs. You will work with business and development teams to design, and document dashboards, alerts, and reports. As BI Engineer you are not only a report builder, you are also a data modeller, steward, and a first-class citizen for data manipulation, ready to answer the question: Can you tell us something that we don’t know?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Think you’ve been challenged before? Think again!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Scale&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;4 million happy shoppers shop online on takealot.com. Show them what you can do.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learn&lt;/strong&gt;: We work with the best of the best, and then some. Code alongside industry leaders and upskill in record time.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow&lt;/strong&gt;: Expand your career in the fast-growing Takealot Group: takealot.com, TFS and Mr D. We like to promote from within: Here’s your chance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who’s who in the tech space&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the relevant BI Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your mission, should you choose to accept it:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead BI analytical projects as part of the implementation of new BI software tools and systems (Google Big Query, Looker).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on highly complex, cross-functional, and enterprise BI solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate internal and external stakeholder needs in order to provide appropriate solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the planning process, technical design, development and testing of BI solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide input to the development of information quality metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review data pipelines and test plans to ensure that business results are tested and correct.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research, identify, analyse, and provide input to new tools, frameworks, techniques, patterns, or processes that will have a positive impact on the BI architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and develop best practices for reports and dashboards deployments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide guidance, training, and problem-solving assistance to other team members.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide subject matter expertise for key BI core functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The skills we need:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to understand a customer&#39;s business needs and translate them into dev requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to anticipate, identify, and define problems- seek root causes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attention to detail and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to collaborate with other members of formal and informal groups in the pursuit of common missions, vision, values, and mutual goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s Degree or Advanced Diploma in Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Management, and a minimum of 5 years of Business Analysis or related technical experience is required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In the event that a candidate does not have a Bachelor’s Degree

&lt;p&gt;takealot.com, South Africa&#39;s leading online retailer, is looking for a highly talented&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Buyer - Computer Components&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team in Cape Town.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a young, dynamic, hyper-growth company looking for smart, creative, hard-working people with integrity to join us. We offer a market-related, Total Remuneration Package which allows full flexibility according to your needs, a great work environment and a promise that you won’t be bored as long as you are prepared for a challenge and want to build something great.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position reports to the Divisonal Buying Manager.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of the role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To select and purchase merchandise, ensuring the right products are available to meet customer demand and maximize sales and profitability.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key responsibilities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a comprehensive &lt;strong&gt;Computer Components &lt;/strong&gt;strategy/plan to drive growth across the department in sales, brands, suppliers and new product listings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan to develop and drive growth across the department in sales, brands, suppliers and new product listings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive innovation by sourcing and prioritizing new brands and suppliers according to this growth plan and in line with market trends and consumer demand&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver against key financial and service level performance indicators within the department (sales, margin, listings availability, stock cover etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and develop supplier relationships, negotiate good prices, improve trading terms and manage suppliers according to strict SLAs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop a promotional programme, source great deals and manage site merchandising for the department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the operations team in delivering a world-class customer experience – monitor department returns, support the customer service team on product queries and resolving any customer complaints&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage stock and availability (including replenishment orders, stock cover)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver on customer experience within the department (ensuring products are delivered on time, supplier terms are aligned, product quality is managed etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Required Qualification&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Diploma/Bachelor’s degree (Business Science or Commerce degree preferable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Required Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3 - 5 years related retail / commerce / e-commerce experience&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Required Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build lasting supplier relationships and manage according to SLAs (existing industry networks a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Great excel knowledge&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skills, knowledge &amp;amp; abilities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solutions-oriented, can-do attitude; self-motivated&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and critical thinking, ability to use data to inform decisions, identify the root cause and resolve problem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong product and buying planning skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage priorities according to clear prioritization and structured planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to build lasting supplier relationships and manage according to SLAs (existing industry networks a plus)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable with change and excellent team player&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about the industry and the potential of e-commerce&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of the key business drivers within online retail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Entrepre

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.takealot.com/&quot;&gt;takealot.com&lt;/a&gt;, South Africa&#39;s leading online retailer, is looking for a highly talented Buyer&#39;s Assistant to join our Retail team in Cape Town.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a young, dynamic, hyper growth company looking for smart, creative, hard-working people with integrity to join us. We offer a market related, Total Remuneration Package which allows full flexibility according to your needs, a great work environment and a promise that you won’t be bored as long as you are prepared for a challenge and want to build something great.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This position reports to the Divisional Buying Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the division in all administrative functions linked to order processing and buy Plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Auditing availability, selection and pricing of market best sellers and new releases on the site.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting on merchandising checks: Checking customer reviews, links and newsletters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing customer queries and escalating as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee day-to-day tasks such as managing stock levels, processing customer orders, handling stock classification, and addressing catalogue-related queries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve stock quality disputes and manage ad hoc issues related to stock, products, deliveries, and other retail operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with suppliers and internal stakeholders to drive the success of the retail category.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possesses excellent verbal and written communication skills, with the confidence to pick up the phone and engage directly with stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be quick to react, proactive in identifying and resolving issues, and demonstrate a hands-on approach to ensuring smooth operations and effective problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualification &amp;amp; Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree (Business Science or Commerce degree preferable).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 1-year related retail / commerce experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An Existing industry networks, a significant plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competency in MS Office packages, particularly Excel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retail buying/e-commerce experience preferable but not an absolute requirement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attributes Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organised with the ability to prioritise tasks effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solutions-oriented with a proactive, can-do attitude; self-motivated and driven.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptable and comfortable with learning and using new systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fast learner with the ability to quickly adapt to new software packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Willingness to learn new systems and expand knowledge in AI-related technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in working with software tools such as Excel, Google Sheets, and Google Docs, with the ability to manage and navigate various digital platforms efficiently&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Environment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; takealot.com employees are entrepreneurial and dynamic, smart, customer- centric, fun and have the shared ambition of takealot.com being the leading e- commerce company in Africa.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.takealot.com/&quot;&gt;takealot.com&lt;/a&gt;, South Africa&#39;s leading online retailer, is looking for a highly talented &lt;strong&gt;Community Manager Lead&lt;/strong&gt; to join our &lt;strong&gt;Personal Shopper Program &lt;/strong&gt;in Cape Town.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Community Manager Lead manages a team of Community Managers to directly support Personal Shoppers, ensuring operational efficiency and the achievement of core business targets&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;strong&gt;The role is directly accountable for growing the monthly active shopper base, maximizing GMV, and improving month-on-month retention by ensuring the team effectively manages the Community Manager Dashboard, drives adoption of the Personal Shopper App, and utilizes internal AI personalization tools.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position reports to the&lt;strong&gt; Head of Personal Shopper Program&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your responsibilities will include:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team Leadership: Manage and coach the Community Manager team, setting clear performance expectations and running bi-weekly KPI check-ins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Active Base &amp;amp; App Adoption: Drive engagement and widespread adoption of the Personal Shopper App to grow and maintain the monthly active shopper base.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;GMV &amp;amp; Dashboard Management: Own the Community Manager Dashboard, ensuring the team feeds it effectively to update the app while leveraging internal AI tools to scale personalized engagement and maximize shopper GMV.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Retention &amp;amp; High-Performer Development: Monitor month-on-month retention, resolve community escalations, and empower high-performing shoppers to scale their businesses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feedback &amp;amp; Product Evolution: Gather insights and app usage data to recommend continuous improvements for program processes, training materials, and internal digital tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Core Commercial &amp;amp; Performance Metrics:&lt;/p&gt;
